mdplay
======
mdplay is a simple music player for the command line. It just plays all files
inside a specified directory.


Requirements
------------
FFmpeg development libraries.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (mdplay is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Additional configurations regarding the software can be done in the
config.h file.

Afterwards, enter the following command to build and install mdplay (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running mdplay
--------------
mdplay [-v] [dir]

